Diagnosis: Integumental papillae rounded or slightly extended, in some cases surrounded by a granulate area of additional small elevations (
Fig. 9 h – k
). Medial margin Cx-I smooth or with very inconspicuous projections near setae bases (
Fig. 9 f – g
). Cx-IV with a relatively long posteromedial apodeme, directed medially ( Fig. 10 b ). Swimming setae numbers (anterior/posterior) II-L-5, 0/0 – 1; III-L-4, 0/5 – 7; III-L-5, 0/4 – 8; IV-L-4, 3 – 7/5 – 8; IV-L-5, 0 [rarely 1 – 2–see remarks]/4 – 6. Leg claws strongly enlarged–length (all legs) 40 – 75 – 18 – 31 % penultimate segment. Leg segments stout (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 3.3 – 3.9; II-L-5, 4.0 – 4.6; III-L-5, 4.0 – 5.1; IV-L-5, 4.7 – 5.6–see
Fig. 10 d–e
).
